It's wide open.

244
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,916
I know this coach. He's a prick.

245
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:31,588
This is a setup. I've seen this.
We'll run it again.

246
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:33,869
Let's do it!

247
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,991
Let's do Deuce Left 22...

248
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:39,516
Run the same play?!

249
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:43,392
All the Sharks have to do
is hold on to the ball.

250
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:46,871
It's money time! Give me five!
We home and dry and flying high.

251
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,958
Let the D win it, J-man.
We don't need no first down.

252
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:52,071
That's why you don't score
with the ladies!

253
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:53,679
Same play. Same play.

254
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:54,756
On two!

255
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:59,989
Call time-out. They're stacked up
against the run.

256
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,031
Time-out's for TV. Negative.

257
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,799
Fumble!

258
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:21,792
He fumbled!

259
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,798
Loose ball! Minnesota's got it.

260
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,672
How stupid! How selfish!

261
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:33,038
Julian Washington fumbles the ball!

262
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,434
In your face!

263
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:41,875
You wonder if the million-dollar
bonus when he reaches 1500 yards...

264
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,559
...didn't play into that one.

265
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:47,230
That's right, Kev. And now D'Amato's
lost four games in a row.

266
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:48,953
Two hands!

267
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,071
With two hands, you showboat!

268
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:55,153
Honey, please don't feel too bad.

269
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:57,393
We lost once.

270
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,238
All of a sudden...

271
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,670
...one of these real tall gentlemen...

272
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,632
...jumped up so high...

273
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:07,469
...and he just picked that thing
out of that air just like that.

274
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,477
And I thought your daddy...

275
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,996
I thought he'd have a heart attack.

276
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:19,156
He died because of this.

277
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,437
I don't want you to take anything
so seriously, honey.

278
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:25,279
-lt's just a game, honey.
-Good night, Mother.

279
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:28,751
-Good night, darling.
-At least the dog still loves her.

280
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:32,029
Make sure she gets home, all right?

281
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,389
No stops.

282
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:34,915
Shall I wait up?

283
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,511
No, I'd be a lousy date tonight.

284
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:40,393
Don't forget I'm in Boston tomorrow
for 2 or 3 days.

285
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:42,431
It's a complicated deposition.

286
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,039
I'm sorry. I forgot.

287
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:50,959
Kick their asses.

288
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,195
Tomorrow morning, first thing.

289
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,198
Make it three.

290
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,989
You want a walk-through?

291
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:03,992
Let it go, Willie.
You played strong.

292
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,513
I'm just sick of losing.

293
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,436
When you're my age,
you get used to it.

294
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,676
All right, everybody, listen up!

295
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,715
Played your hearts out there today.

296
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:20,396
No blame, nobody.

297
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:21,914
Let's take a knee. Father.

298
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:30,476
You and I have been in some tough
places together, haven't we?

299
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,438
I went to my playbook.

300
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:39,513
And the book says the rain falls
on the just and the unjust alike.

301
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,916
Now, we just lost four in a row.

302
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:47,671
That doesn't mean
that we're specially cursed.

303
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,793
Joy comes in the morning.

304
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,916
There are no atheists in foxholes.

305
00:21:58,640 --> 00:21:59,834
Let's pray.

306
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:03,515
"Our Father, who art in Heaven..."

307
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,753
-How you doing, Rock?
-I felt like I was gonna die.

308
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:19,592
They went in and they sucked out...

309
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,633
...my L-5 disk.

310
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,508
It's no big deal.

311
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,714
-Did we win?
-They beat us by three.

312
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,035
What'd the kid throw?

313
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,708
Nine of 14 for 176.

314
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,434
TDs?

315
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:35,876
Two.

316
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:37,394
Holy moly!

317
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:41,913
I can beat this.

318
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:45,319
Cindy, will you please call that nurse?!

319
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:49,513
This doesn't work! I'm a football
player! They gotta pump up the volume!

320
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:52,514
Breathe.

321
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,068
Don't overachieve.

322
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,838
Even at 50%%%, nobody's better.

323
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:57,439
Playoffs...

324
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,159
...l'll be ready.

325
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:06,071
It's getting late. I'm gonna stop by
in the morning. You get some rest.

326
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:08,197
-Good night, Cindy.
-Good night.

327
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,673
Don't you give up on me.

328
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,950
You're like a son to me, Cap.

329
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:20,714
I'll fight for you till the day I die.

330
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:27,712
Willie Beamen, I don't believe you.

331
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:32,516
Your first big game on TV,
and you didn't let your own mama know!

332
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,313
Here it is right here.

333
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:37,711
Not that Willie didn't have some
nauseating moments of his own.

334
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,235
Poor guy!

335
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:47,230
Are you gonna start?
You could at least play first-string.

336
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:48,555
No, probably not.

337
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,399
Let's hope Willie Beamen
brings his Tums with him.

338
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,875
-You should be starting.
-Mom, I'm number three.

339
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:56,275
There ain't nothing
I can do about it.

340
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,078
You've been at this for 5 years!

341
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:01,078
Tell everybody I said I love them,
and I'll see them.

342
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,709
-I love you too, Willie.
-I love you.

343
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:07,872
Baby, she just wants the best for you.

344
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:10,279
Yeah, I know she does.

345
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,833
You did great!

346
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:36,354
You gotta wonder why D'Amato
would call that play...

347
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:39,279
... when J-man likes to pick his spot
when he runs.

348
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:41,829
Calling the same play twice?
What's that about?

349
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:44,998
There's a reason this team's
lost four games in a row.

350
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:47,593
Forget about the offensive line.

351
00:24:48,040 --> 00:24:49,314
And forget about Cap Rooney.

352
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:52,273
Forget about the money-grubbing
Christina Pagniacci.

353
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,310
Hello, genius!

354
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:57,869
This guy started coaching
in the late '60s, for God's sake!

355
00:24:58,080 --> 00:24:59,559
I'm glad he's not talking about me.

356
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:01,591
-Here you go, coach.
-Thank you.

357
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:05,873
This is a team with more than 200
variations on the pass!

358
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:09,311
Napoleon D'Amato's playbook's
got less than 75 plays, total!

359
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:13,149
200 variations on a pass!
What's wrong with this picture?

360
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,550
You're that coach, right?

361
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,996
I'm Mandy. Mandy Murphy.

362
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:25,315
You look better in real life.
You're always yelling at people on TV.

363
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,958
At least I look better
than that old fart up there, no?

364
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:35,028
I think.

365
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:36,789
You do.

366
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:40,193
-How old are you?
-I don't think age matters.

367
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:42,960
I think older guys have a certain thing.

368
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:46,232
I've wanted to meet you since I was 16.

369
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:49,392
You were on the sidelines.
You were winning this big game.

370
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:51,836
The Pantheon Cup, yeah.

371
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:54,680
That was it.
God, that's so wild!

372
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:57,791
So you promise to keep a secret?

373
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:09,315
I don't know. How do you mean?
On a date?

374
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,513
I got a place.

375
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:15,597
It's close by. It's quiet.

376
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:17,314
It's a thousand.

377
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:20,990
Five thousand for the night.
You won't regret it.

378
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:23,276
I'm flattered, thank you, but...

379
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:29,793
I got friends.
I could do your friends too.

380
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:32,396
-Some other time maybe.
-Fair enough.

381
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:35,311
Good luck.
I'll be rooting for you.

382
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:37,630
-Thank you.
-Coach.

383
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:44,192
I know you're not gonna
pass on that, D'Amato.

384
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:47,872
I must be drunk.

385
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,796
...Christina Pagniacci,
who's so smart...

386
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:54,470
...she sold three of last year's
starters in the off-season.

387
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:56,989
You think you can lose
your coaching instincts?

388
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:59,475
You never had them.
How you gonna lose them?

389
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:06,198
All I got are my instincts.
I lose those, I got nothing.

390
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:25,437
Please leave your name and message
and we'll get right back to you.

391
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,995
Have a nice day. Bye-bye.

392
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,393
So, Jeanette...

393
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:33,950
I was hoping you'd be awake.

394
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:36,910
What time is it out there, anyway?

395
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:40,993
Never mind.

396
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:45,473
Could you tell Tommy that I'll be
in L.A. in a couple of weeks?

397
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:47,079
We got a game.

398
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:49,954
I'd like to get together with him...

399
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:53,076
...but I don't have his new number.

400
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:58,474
I really miss the shit out of
little Timmy and Melinda.

401
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:00,909
And you.

402
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,113
Grandkids.

403
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,313
We got grandkids.

404
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:12,676
Why did we get divorced anyway?

405
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:14,434
Fuck!

406
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:18,557
If you'd like to make a call,
please hang up and try again.

407
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,269
Shit!

408
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,870
We're gonna make a difference
this week!

409
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:44,396
Just the tip of the ball. Catch it!

410
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:47,872
This ain't no bullshit West Virginia.
You in the big leagues!

411
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:52,793
What the fuck is that? What are you,
a pussy? That ain't no damn hit.

412
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:56,515
-14 years, I know how to hit.
-14 years, you're captain.

413
00:28:58,480 --> 00:28:59,515
Show me!

414
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,432
Break that shit up!

415
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,033
Goddamn it, baby! You did it!

416
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:11,151
That's my boy, my brotherfucker!

417
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:14,836
That's the way to hit it, Shark.
That is the way to hit it.

418
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,598
Now, come on in here.

419
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,753
Let me get this straight.

420
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:22,839
The California governor says there's
nothing for the public to vote on?

421
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:26,476
She's got the finances to build
a new stadium in Los Angeles...

422
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,749
...using lottery money.

423
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:29,479
Jeez, Ed!

424
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:31,711
L.A.'s a dream.

425
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:37,550
Certainly good enough to leverage the
city of Miami into a new stadium.

426
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:42,631
What about the Rosenthal bid?

427
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:44,398
$250 million?

428
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:48,029
It's so low.

429
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:50,278
With a new stadium and a winning team...

430
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:52,631
...this club is worth $800 million.

431
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,399
It's me!

432
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:58,998
You're like your dad.
You're a dreamer.

433
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:00,155
Take the money!

434
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:04,917
You're still young, darling.
Start over. Start a family.

435
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,918
You don't love football anyway.

436
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,838
It's none of your business, Ed.

437
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:13,078
Let's keep this between the three of us.

438
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,711
-Morning, Tony.
-Morning, Christina.

439
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,389
Alka-Seltzer?

440
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:24,280
No, thank you.
I had about four for breakfast.

441
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,195
This is a hell of a loss, Tony.

442
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:32,557
I can see how my mom could drink herself
into a stupor watching football games.

443
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:36,509
But this kind of play makes me
want to jump out of a window.

444
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:42,110
Well, you can run this a billion times,
but on any given Sunday...

445
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:44,197
"You'll either win or you'll lose.

446
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:47,671
The point is, can you win or lose
like a man?" Dad said lots of things.

447
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,154
Actually, I said that.

448
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:51,431
But he could never stand losing.

449
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:55,189
And Julian couldn't resist
going for his bonus yards.

450
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:57,908
Blame me, not Julian.
That was my call.

451
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,758
I know it was, Tony.

452
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:01,598
It's four in a row.

453
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,119
This season is a disaster.

454
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:06,788
Without the playoffs,
there's no more TV money.

455
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:08,319
You see this?

456
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,715
They want your head.

457
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:12,639
Your father would laugh at them.
This is a good team.

458
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,159
We hit, we win.

459
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,152
We put pressure, we win.

460
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:20,473
We penetrate, we win. You do it as
tough as it is possible to do!

461
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:23,235
And you do that in all things.

462
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:25,237
You die hard.

463
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:28,075
That's what I'm talking about.
You die hard.

464
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,749
Dad used to say:

465
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:32,636
"No intensity, no victory."

466
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:35,149
Where the hell is your intensity,
Tony?

467
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:38,637
Four years ago,
we won the Pantheon Cup!

468
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,715
-I was there, remember?
-Now what are we?

469
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:45,913
We're a second-tier team, that's what.

470
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,914
Admit it! You're not being honest!

471
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:53,472
We're a solid football team.
We're just not inspired.

472
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:56,638
Too many free agents.
We got Julian. He's a merc.

473
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:57,909
End of the season, he's gone.

474
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:00,395
Next year, we rebuild our running game.

475
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:04,115
You talk about a running game, but
who cares as long as you're winning?

476
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:07,392
People want to see passes, touchdowns.

477
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:09,795
High scores. That's the game today.

478
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:13,792
I paid a lot of money
to get Nick Crozier here...

479
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:15,917
...specifically to modernize...

480
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:18,714
Football's played on a field,
not in the goddamn boxes.

481
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:21,753
You knew that when you had candy
stuck in your braces.

482
00:32:21,960 --> 00:32:24,428
If we had gotten the linemen I wanted...

483
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:26,596
...our first two quarterbacks
would still be walking.

484
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:28,199
Think of the future.

485
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:31,036
Do you know what we could get for Cap?

486
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:35,438
Probably a second
and a third-draft choice.

487
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:38,555
We know that he's finished but...

488
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:41,235
I don't know that Cap is finished.

489
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:45,274
Do I have to remind you
that he helped build this franchise?

490
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:47,755
He's a hero to the working people
of Florida!

491
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:51,398
Probably one of the greatest pressure
players of all time.

492
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:52,715
You can't cut Cap...

493
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:55,388
Cap and Shark were great,
but memories...

494
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:58,194
