should've told me. I had four weeks.

1467
01:36:09,880 --> 01:36:11,757
I could've gone another way!

1468
01:36:12,480 --> 01:36:13,595
I'm sorry.

1469
01:36:20,680 --> 01:36:23,956
I got blank spots in my memory.
It's weird.

1470
01:36:25,080 --> 01:36:27,150
And I shake.

1471
01:36:28,680 --> 01:36:31,831
Sometimes I can't even hold a spoon.

1472
01:36:33,240 --> 01:36:36,994
And I'm always on painkillers
for my elbow...

1473
01:36:37,240 --> 01:36:39,754
...or my rib or my neck!

1474
01:36:39,960 --> 01:36:42,554
Now I got this ruptured disc,
and I just...

1475
01:36:45,880 --> 01:36:48,678
Even with all that,
I would go back in a second...

1476
01:36:51,920 --> 01:36:53,672
But if I go in there, Tony...

1477
01:36:56,680 --> 01:36:58,238
...l'm gonna fold.

1478
01:36:59,440 --> 01:37:00,759
And I just...

1479
01:37:04,640 --> 01:37:06,232
I can't do that.

1480
01:37:09,640 --> 01:37:11,995
You know these things you're saying...

1481
01:37:13,080 --> 01:37:14,672
...all in your head, Rock.

1482
01:37:15,640 --> 01:37:17,119
They're not real.

1483
01:37:17,880 --> 01:37:19,359
You understand?

1484
01:37:19,920 --> 01:37:21,990
You know you got it in you...

1485
01:37:23,400 --> 01:37:24,879
...because I know you do.

1486
01:37:28,320 --> 01:37:29,833
It's my body, Tony.

1487
01:37:30,040 --> 01:37:31,439
It's my body. It's not there.

1488
01:37:31,640 --> 01:37:33,232
I wouldn't let you get hurt.

1489
01:37:33,880 --> 01:37:35,359
I need you, Rock...

1490
01:37:37,200 --> 01:37:38,952
...to lead this team.

1491
01:37:41,480 --> 01:37:42,674
Come on.

1492
01:37:43,520 --> 01:37:44,748
One more time.

1493
01:37:45,680 --> 01:37:46,954
You and me.

1494
01:37:47,760 --> 01:37:49,910
You and me, together.

1495
01:37:52,000 --> 01:37:53,228
Trust me.

1496
01:37:58,840 --> 01:38:01,070
You need me, Tony, I'll be there.

1497
01:38:01,680 --> 01:38:02,749
Thank you.

1498
01:38:05,400 --> 01:38:07,311
What I'm saying is...

1499
01:38:08,080 --> 01:38:11,675
...l've got my rings,
we took care of our money...

1500
01:38:12,560 --> 01:38:14,676
...and the kids are all right.

1501
01:38:16,640 --> 01:38:19,598
We had a good run.
I just think that it's time for me...

1502
01:38:20,480 --> 01:38:22,948
...to get out after this season.

1503
01:38:23,520 --> 01:38:24,919
And do what?

1504
01:38:25,800 --> 01:38:28,314
I talked to a guy
at one of the networks...

1505
01:38:28,520 --> 01:38:30,556
You are a football player.

1506
01:38:31,800 --> 01:38:33,677
Will you hear me out?

1507
01:38:33,880 --> 01:38:35,598
You're a football player, Jack.

1508
01:38:35,800 --> 01:38:39,634
And you have two or three years
left in you.

1509
01:38:40,840 --> 01:38:44,469
Cindy, you are missing
the big picture here.

1510
01:38:44,680 --> 01:38:47,592
There is no big picture here, Jack!

1511
01:38:47,800 --> 01:38:50,633
You're the goddamn quarterback
for the Miami Sharks!

1512
01:38:50,840 --> 01:38:53,593
You're a legend,
and you're talking about quitting?

1513
01:38:54,400 --> 01:38:58,359
All my life everybody's been telling me
what to do, ever since college!

1514
01:38:58,560 --> 01:39:01,074
This is not your decision!
It is my decision...!

1515
01:39:02,560 --> 01:39:05,836
I will not listen
to this bullshit from you!

1516
01:39:06,480 --> 01:39:07,754
I will not!

1517
01:39:26,880 --> 01:39:27,676
Wanna know why?

1518
01:39:27,880 --> 01:39:30,474
Because they want you.
You know what I'm saying?

1519
01:39:30,680 --> 01:39:32,193
The sky's the limit, baby.

1520
01:39:32,400 --> 01:39:34,709
They'll swallow
the beer distributorship.

1521
01:39:34,920 --> 01:39:37,639
The funny thing about this
whole situation is...

1522
01:39:37,840 --> 01:39:40,115
...no one knows how good
you really are.

1523
01:39:40,320 --> 01:39:43,676
You get in that playoff game,
you score...

1524
01:39:44,080 --> 01:39:46,674
...you can forget about this team.
They'll lose anyway.

1525
01:39:46,880 --> 01:39:48,438
-I'm bored.
-Can you give me a second?

1526
01:39:48,640 --> 01:39:51,837
You'll get five million
serious dollars from somebody.

1527
01:39:52,080 --> 01:39:54,116
I'm gonna tell you something else.

1528
01:39:54,360 --> 01:39:57,238
Christina wants to give you $2 million
to extend you for the year.

1529
01:39:57,840 --> 01:39:59,114
But we're gonna wait.

1530
01:39:59,640 --> 01:40:02,950
That's what you hired me for,
to watch your back.

1531
01:40:03,160 --> 01:40:04,275
You follow me?

1532
01:40:04,480 --> 01:40:06,357
I hope you're doing that, Wayne.

1533
01:40:07,320 --> 01:40:09,515
Just in case I ain't made out of steel.

1534
01:40:10,040 --> 01:40:12,270
I'm saying, what if
my arm starts hurting?

1535
01:40:12,480 --> 01:40:14,072
Where you coming from with that?

1536
01:40:14,440 --> 01:40:17,079
Baby, ain't nothing
gonna fall apart on you.

1537
01:40:17,640 --> 01:40:18,436
Vanessa!

1538
01:40:19,320 --> 01:40:20,435
"Vanessa"?

1539
01:40:21,640 --> 01:40:23,119
Excuse me.

1540
01:40:23,360 --> 01:40:24,873
Hey, that's Willie Beamen!

1541
01:40:30,520 --> 01:40:32,238
How you been? Long time.

1542
01:40:32,880 --> 01:40:34,359
Congratulations.

1543
01:40:35,920 --> 01:40:38,070
-Things are cool.
-Getting what you wanted?

1544
01:40:38,400 --> 01:40:39,913
I blew it, V.

1545
01:40:40,240 --> 01:40:43,915
Everything was just happening so fast,
I didn't have time to think.

1546
01:40:44,480 --> 01:40:48,075
I was thinking maybe we could go out,
we could just get together.

1547
01:40:49,720 --> 01:40:51,915
I don't think so, Willie. I'm sorry.

1548
01:40:53,440 --> 01:40:55,158
I understand. Or do I?

1549
01:40:55,640 --> 01:40:57,232
You're just too volatile for me.

1550
01:40:57,480 --> 01:40:59,630
I'm a simple girl.
I like simple things.

1551
01:40:59,840 --> 01:41:03,469
Truth be told, I didn't even
like football. I liked you.

1552
01:41:03,680 --> 01:41:04,908
I'm sorry.

1553
01:41:05,680 --> 01:41:07,193
-I understand...
-Willie, no!

1554
01:41:18,880 --> 01:41:21,633
-Get out of here!
-I need to talk to you.

1555
01:41:21,840 --> 01:41:23,478
Oh, my goodness, Barbara Bush.

1556
01:41:23,840 --> 01:41:26,354
-Where you been all my life?
-I'm sorry.

1557
01:41:27,000 --> 01:41:28,797
You're looking good too!

1558
01:41:29,000 --> 01:41:31,150
There's that smile
I've been looking for.

1559
01:41:31,480 --> 01:41:35,109
Listen to me. I just need to know
that I can call you.

1560
01:41:36,200 --> 01:41:39,670
Tell me that I can call you,
or I'll never talk to you again.

1561
01:41:39,960 --> 01:41:41,791
You're so full of shit.

1562
01:41:42,000 --> 01:41:44,309
No, I'm not. I'm very serious.

1563
01:41:44,640 --> 01:41:45,868
Don't test me.

1564
01:41:47,360 --> 01:41:50,511
You can call me as long as
you get out of here! Now go!

1565
01:41:50,720 --> 01:41:51,914
Get out of here!

1566
01:41:52,120 --> 01:41:54,190
-You too shy?
-No, I'm not shy!

1567
01:41:54,440 --> 01:41:55,873
I got a date out there.

1568
01:41:56,080 --> 01:41:58,674
You're talking about
the mortician out there?

1569
01:41:59,160 --> 01:42:01,469
You're just jealous because he's tall.

1570
01:42:02,320 --> 01:42:03,799
But he can't ball.

1571
01:42:05,240 --> 01:42:06,798
I'll holler.

1572
01:42:10,800 --> 01:42:11,710
Congratulations.

1573
01:42:12,440 --> 01:42:13,839
Was I the last to know?

1574
01:42:14,040 --> 01:42:15,632
Cindy Rooney told me.

1575
01:42:16,000 --> 01:42:18,309
What the hell are you doing
starting Cap?

1576
01:42:18,520 --> 01:42:21,318
Throwing him against the best
pass rush in the league?

1577
01:42:21,520 --> 01:42:22,509
Cap's my starter.

1578
01:42:22,720 --> 01:42:24,915
-lf we lose this game...
-I'll do you one better.

1579
01:42:25,120 --> 01:42:27,076
In the off-season, I'm trading Willie.

1580
01:42:27,320 --> 01:42:28,753
That's not your option.

1581
01:42:28,960 --> 01:42:33,476
Your kid may sell a lot of T-shirts,
but he is tearing this team apart!

1582
01:42:33,680 --> 01:42:35,796
-Then hold it together!
-I can't! Not with him.

1583
01:42:36,000 --> 01:42:36,876
Where are you going?

1584
01:42:37,080 --> 01:42:39,640
You will start Willie on Sunday...

1585
01:42:39,840 --> 01:42:42,149
...and you'll make the adjustment
to modern times.

1586
01:42:42,400 --> 01:42:43,958
You don't tell me what to do.

1587
01:42:44,200 --> 01:42:45,679
Nobody tells me what to do!

1588
01:42:45,880 --> 01:42:49,475
Your father never told me what to do!
You're not gonna start!

1589
01:42:49,680 --> 01:42:52,797
I'd cut my father's ass
if we were losing like this.

1590
01:42:53,000 --> 01:42:56,595
You know, I'm really getting
sick and tired of you.

1591
01:42:56,920 --> 01:42:58,990
Your father was no genius.

1592
01:42:59,360 --> 01:43:01,351
He only acted like he was one.

1593
01:43:01,600 --> 01:43:04,717
And he took credit for a lot of things
he never did!

1594
01:43:04,920 --> 01:43:06,990
He at least respected me.

1595
01:43:07,200 --> 01:43:10,192
Would you stop using my father
as a scapegoat?

1596
01:43:11,520 --> 01:43:14,830
I can't even imagine what he'd think
of you right now...

1597
01:43:15,040 --> 01:43:18,715
...but my hunch is, he'd be ashamed.
He'd be ashamed!

1598
01:43:18,920 --> 01:43:22,629
Why do you think he put me in charge,
you bullheaded moron?

1599
01:43:22,840 --> 01:43:26,037
He could've made you general manager,
but he didn't, did he?

1600
01:43:26,240 --> 01:43:27,719
You know why?

1601
01:43:27,920 --> 01:43:31,799
Because he knew you didn't have the guts
to do it after he was gone!

1602
01:43:40,520 --> 01:43:43,398
It's true, Tony.
He couldn't trust you.

1603
01:43:44,160 --> 01:43:45,513
You got old.

1604
01:44:17,080 --> 01:44:19,150
I'll be in my father's office.

1605
01:44:26,240 --> 01:44:29,516
-Christina will destroy this team.
-What is it you fear?

1606
01:44:30,800 --> 01:44:33,837
You've got so much fear
inside of you, Tony.

1607
01:44:35,960 --> 01:44:38,110
I'm losing the team, Maggie.

1608
01:44:38,840 --> 01:44:40,717
I'm losing control.

1609
01:44:42,920 --> 01:44:44,831
Everything in my life's about control.

1610
01:44:45,040 --> 01:44:46,189
I lead men.

1611
01:44:46,880 --> 01:44:48,518
I control.

1612
01:44:51,520 --> 01:44:53,351
Did Art think I was past it?

1613
01:44:54,920 --> 01:44:56,114
I don't know.

1614
01:44:57,840 --> 01:44:59,159
Do you care?

1615
01:44:59,440 --> 01:45:02,238
You never understood Artie,
did you?

1616
01:45:03,120 --> 01:45:05,429
He wanted a son...

1617
01:45:05,680 --> 01:45:08,114
...more than anything else
in the world.

1618
01:45:09,440 --> 01:45:13,558
And when you really think about it,
what Christina is...

1619
01:45:13,840 --> 01:45:15,956
...it's just such a tragedy.

1620
01:45:18,000 --> 01:45:20,912
You know, she will sell the team.

1621
01:45:21,560 --> 01:45:24,154
And everything her father
stood for is gonna die.

1622
01:45:26,840 --> 01:45:30,799
And what will you do, Tony,
after football...

1623
01:45:31,560 --> 01:45:34,154
...with nobody to control?

1624
01:45:34,840 --> 01:45:36,717
Stop it. What are you doing?

1625
01:45:37,480 --> 01:45:40,233
Hey, I blame you for a lot of things.

1626
01:45:41,920 --> 01:45:44,639
You were like Artie.

1627
01:45:45,440 --> 01:45:47,078
A monster.

1628
01:45:48,360 --> 01:45:51,238
You've gotten older. Better.

1629
01:45:54,440 --> 01:45:57,079
But for a long time I hated you.

1630
01:45:59,520 --> 01:46:02,876
That game took my husband,
my daughter...

1631
01:46:03,080 --> 01:46:04,672
...my youth.

1632
01:46:04,920 --> 01:46:06,194
Left me with what?

1633
01:46:07,000 --> 01:46:10,515
All those Sunday afternoons
at the stadium.

1634
01:46:11,680 --> 01:46:13,432
And time...

1635
01:46:15,000 --> 01:46:17,639
...just kept slipping away, didn't it?

1636
01:46:27,400 --> 01:46:28,719
How's your head, Jack?

1637
01:46:28,920 --> 01:46:33,311
Sandy, it's nice of you to ask.
It's still hurting, quite frankly.

1638
01:46:33,560 --> 01:46:35,516
Like you guys, I play hurt.

1639
01:46:35,960 --> 01:46:38,872
Look at the monitor, you'll see
it was more than aggression.

1640
01:46:39,080 --> 01:46:41,150
Out of my way!

1641
01:46:41,920 --> 01:46:43,797
Well, that's just great.

1642
01:47:03,400 --> 01:47:07,678
There goes D'Amato, his 14th
consecutive game with a touchdown!

1643
01:47:08,200 --> 01:47:12,591
We regret to inform you that your
husband, Lieutenant Louis D'Amato...

1644
01:47:12,800 --> 01:47:15,519
... was killed in the European
theater of operations.

1645
01:47:15,720 --> 01:47:18,439
And to your son, Anthony D'Amato...

1646
01:47:19,000 --> 01:47:20,991
...our deepest regrets.

1647
01:48:14,240 --> 01:48:17,596
Controversy swirls around
the six-point Shark underdogs.

1648
01:48:17,800 --> 01:48:22,237
Willie "Steamin"' Beamen,
the sensational quarterback...

1649
01:48:22,520 --> 01:48:25,353
... who's held the Sharks together,
is not starting.

1650
01:48:25,560 --> 01:48:28,711
He's said to be feuding
with his beleaguered coach...

1651
01:48:28,920 --> 01:48:32,117
... who's being investigated
for hitting Jack Rose...

1652
01:48:32,320 --> 01:48:34,231
...earlier this week at practice.

1653
01:48:37,360 --> 01:48:39,476
I'd say that's
a bit of an exaggeration.

1654
01:48:39,680 --> 01:48:41,398
-A mild shove.
-We'll find out later.

1655
01:48:41,600 --> 01:48:44,239
I'm the best yard receiver
that's ever lived.

1656
01:48:44,480 --> 01:48:46,436
I can catch anything.

1657
01:48:46,680 --> 01:48:50,036
I'm the best receiver
that's ever lived.

1658
01:48:51,160 --> 01:48:52,354
That's right.

1659
01:48:52,640 --> 01:48:55,552
Meanwhile, Tug,
immortal but vulnerable Cap Rooney...

1660
01:48:55,760 --> 01:48:58,638
...only six weeks off
a microdiskectomy...

1661
01:49:00,600 --> 01:49:03,592
...will start against
the league's toughest pass rush.

1662
01:49:03,800 --> 01:49:05,313
-"Toughest"?
-The toughest.

1663
01:49:05,520 --> 01:49:08,830
Get ready for the sparks to fly.
We'll be right back.

1664
01:49:12,000 --> 01:49:14,275
"The tension of the season
got to me...

1665
01:49:14,480 --> 01:49:18,029
...and I overreacted to an innocent
question from a journalist...

1666
01:49:18,280 --> 01:49:20,271
...we all know to be
of the highest caliber.

1667
01:49:20,480 --> 01:49:24,598
I only hope that one day I'll truly
be able to show Jack Rose...

1668
01:49:24,800 --> 01:49:27,792
...just how much I treasure
his invaluable contribution...

1669
01:49:28,000 --> 01:49:29,797
...to the sport of football."

1670
01:49:31,560 --> 01:49:32,788
Thank you.

1671
01:49:35,600 --> 01:49:36,953
Where's your wheelchair?

1672
01:49:37,520 --> 01:49:39,033
Hello, commissioner.

1673
01:49:41,680 --> 01:49:43,238
God, I hate Texas.

1674
01:49:47,680 --> 01:49:49,272
How are the headaches?

1675
01:49:49,480 --> 01:49:51,516
Fine, till you start doing that shit.

1676
01:49:52,440 --> 01:49:53,555
Your balance?

1677
01:49:53,760 --> 01:49:55,432
My check balance?

1678
01:49:55,640 --> 01:49:58,154
Looking P-H-A-T, baby. Phat.

1679
01:49:58,760 --> 01:50:00,751
Go on, get out of here.
You're done.

1680
01:50:02,120 --> 01:50:03,758
How about another shot, doc?

1681
01:50:03,960 --> 01:50:07,077
You don't need it.
It doesn't make any sense...

1682
01:50:07,480 --> 01:50:08,356
...medically.

1683
01:50:08,560 --> 01:50:12,951
Don't give a shit about medical, doc.
Give me some of that cortisone shit.

1684
01:50:13,880 --> 01:50:15,074
Please?

1685
01:50:30,480 --> 01:50:34,473
The surviving team will move on
next week to Minnesota...

1686
01:50:34,680 --> 01:50:37,831
...cold country for the
AFFA conference championship.

1687
01:50:38,160 --> 01:50:41,470
In the meantime,
we're back to another dang commercial.

1688
01:50:46,000 --> 01:50:48,309
I don't know what to say, really.

1689
01:50:50,680 --> 01:50:51,715
Three minutes...

1690
01:50:53,040 --> 01:50:55,759
...till the biggest battle
of our professional lives.

1691
01:50:56,920 --> 01:50:58,512
All comes down to today.

1692
01:51:01,520 --> 01:51:04,318
Either we heal as a team...

1693
01:51:05,640 --> 01:51:07,153
...or we're gonna crumble.

1694
01:51:08,200 --> 01:51:12,478
Inch by inch, play by play,
till we're finished.

1695
01:51:12,680 --> 01:51:14,989
We're in hell right now, gentlemen.

1696
01:51:15,480 --> 01:51:16,515
Believe me.

1697
01:51:18,840 --> 01:51:22,150
And we can stay here,
get the shit kicked out of us...

1698
01:51:23,960 --> 01:51:27,669
...or we can fight our way
back into the light.

1699
01:51:28,320 --> 01:51:30,390
We can climb out of hell...

1700
01:51:31,800 --> 01:51:33,995
...one inch at a time.

1701
01:51:36,240 --> 01:51:38,708
Now, I can't do it for you.

1702
01:51:38,920 --> 01:51:40,114
I'm too old.

1703
01:51:42,480 --> 01:51:46,359
I look around, I see these
young faces, and I think...

1704
01:51:48,520 --> 01:51:52,115
...I made every wrong choice
a middle-aged man can make.

1705
01:51:55,720 --> 01:51:58,996
I pissed away all my money,
believe it or not.

1706
01:52:00,440 --> 01:52:03,591
I chased off anyone
who's ever loved me.

1707
01:52:05,600 --> 01:52:10,116
And lately, I can't even stand
the face I see in the mirror.

1708
01:52:14,600 --> 01:52:18,639
You know, when you get old in life,
things get taken from you.

1709
01:52:18,840 --> 01:52:20,831
I mean, that's part of life.

1710
01:52:21,720 --> 01:52:25,076
But you only learn that
when you start losing stuff.

1711
01:52:26,800 --> 01:52:29,473
You find out life's this game
of inches.

