Out-of-bounds on the 3!

1964
02:16:11,400 --> 02:16:14,312
Unselfish! Unselfish!
Way to go, Julian!

1965
02:16:24,120 --> 02:16:26,156
You hear that? That's four seconds.

1966
02:16:31,880 --> 02:16:33,791
Time-out called by the Knights.

1967
02:16:34,400 --> 02:16:36,470
Dallas 35, Miami 31.

1968
02:16:36,720 --> 02:16:39,234
Now, remember,
see it before you do it.

1969
02:16:39,840 --> 02:16:41,319
Julian gave you the shot.

1970
02:16:41,520 --> 02:16:43,238
Make them believe, Willie.

1971
02:16:43,440 --> 02:16:45,317
This time, now.

1972
02:16:47,360 --> 02:16:49,476
One on one, man on man.

1973
02:16:49,680 --> 02:16:51,591
We do it together, all right?

1974
02:16:51,800 --> 02:16:53,438
I know y'all don't wanna go home.

1975
02:16:53,760 --> 02:16:54,795
It ain't no tomorrow!

1976
02:17:06,600 --> 02:17:09,353
Three yards to go. Four seconds.
One play.

1977
02:17:10,040 --> 02:17:11,792
We've been in too many of these.

1978
02:17:12,400 --> 02:17:13,389
This one'll get it.

1979
02:17:13,600 --> 02:17:14,828
Four seconds.

1980
02:17:15,880 --> 02:17:17,950
Four seconds is a lifetime!

1981
02:17:18,200 --> 02:17:20,156
We're a lifetime away here!

1982
02:17:25,720 --> 02:17:27,153
Rifle 22!

1983
02:18:17,320 --> 02:18:19,072
I think he lost it!
It didn't go!

1984
02:18:29,800 --> 02:18:31,552
Watch out! Watch out!

1985
02:18:31,920 --> 02:18:32,750
Touchdown!

1986
02:18:37,480 --> 02:18:39,436
Touchdown! Touchdown!

1987
02:19:46,600 --> 02:19:47,669
Nice night.

1988
02:19:49,600 --> 02:19:51,158
Can't get over Cap.

1989
02:19:52,840 --> 02:19:56,549
I learned more watching him in the
first half than I did in five seasons.

1990
02:19:57,480 --> 02:19:59,471
Next week I'll win it
just for him.

1991
02:20:01,000 --> 02:20:05,596
Glad to see success hasn't
gone to your head too much, kid.

1992
02:20:05,800 --> 02:20:08,075
Who, me? Steamin' Beamen?

1993
02:20:10,640 --> 02:20:12,198
This is your moment, Willie.

1994
02:20:13,160 --> 02:20:14,388
Savor it.

1995
02:20:15,840 --> 02:20:20,516
But never forget. On any given Sunday,
you're either gonna win or lose.

1996
02:20:21,080 --> 02:20:24,390
"But can you win or lose like a man?"
I got it, coach.

1997
02:20:34,760 --> 02:20:36,193
Next year...

1998
02:20:36,760 --> 02:20:38,318
...l'm out of here.

1999
02:20:41,640 --> 02:20:42,834
I figured.

2000
02:20:46,040 --> 02:20:48,679
I'm not the right guy
for this team anymore.

2001
02:20:49,000 --> 02:20:50,513
I wouldn't say all that.

2002
02:20:51,240 --> 02:20:54,789
There was this great quarterback
in the '70s I knew.

2003
02:20:55,000 --> 02:20:58,515
I mean, this guy was one tough
son of a bitch.

2004
02:20:58,720 --> 02:21:01,393
He fought for every inch he ever got.

2005
02:21:01,720 --> 02:21:05,679
He didn't have your natural skills,
but he could make it happen.

2006
02:21:05,880 --> 02:21:08,872
He could win.
But the game passed him by.

2007
02:21:09,400 --> 02:21:11,630
Anyway, I ran into this guy...

2008
02:21:12,600 --> 02:21:14,511
...a few weeks ago in L.A.

2009
02:21:14,720 --> 02:21:18,679
We had a few beers, and we start
talking. You know what he told me?

2010
02:21:19,960 --> 02:21:21,552
He said when he looked back...

2011
02:21:21,760 --> 02:21:24,911
...he didn't really miss
the Pantheon Cups...

2012
02:21:25,360 --> 02:21:26,713
...or the girls...

2013
02:21:27,120 --> 02:21:28,348
...or even the glory.

2014
02:21:28,600 --> 02:21:30,033
You know what he missed?

2015
02:21:31,240 --> 02:21:35,711
What he missed were those other guys
looking back at him in the huddle.

2016
02:21:36,920 --> 02:21:38,194
Those eleven guys...

2017
02:21:39,440 --> 02:21:42,238
...every one of them seeing things
the same way.

2018
02:21:42,640 --> 02:21:44,915
All of them looking downfield...

2019
02:21:45,360 --> 02:21:46,554
...together.

2020
02:21:47,720 --> 02:21:49,233
That's what he missed.

2021
02:21:52,320 --> 02:21:54,038
I'm gonna miss you, amigo.

2022
02:22:09,680 --> 02:22:13,753
You know, my arm has been killing me.
I met with a specialist who said...

2023
02:22:20,520 --> 02:22:21,953
I'm scared.

2024
02:22:29,440 --> 02:22:30,429
We're all scared.

2025
02:22:30,640 --> 02:22:34,599
If you think it's easy being a coach,
I'll trade your microphone for my ulcer.

2026
02:22:34,800 --> 02:22:36,995
I'm a triple-decker
stress sandwich right now.

2027
02:22:37,240 --> 02:22:40,915
Why is that, coach?
The 32-13 loss to San Francisco?

2028
02:22:41,160 --> 02:22:44,709
You're not even close, Johnny.
Try fishing someplace else.

2029
02:22:44,920 --> 02:22:48,356
And I want to live up to what it is
my father left me.

2030
02:22:48,800 --> 02:22:50,199
A legacy.

2031
02:22:50,480 --> 02:22:53,074
A feeling of a bond with this town.

2032
02:22:53,320 --> 02:22:55,515
A feeling that this is our house.

2033
02:22:55,720 --> 02:22:57,790
The Pagniacci house.

2034
02:23:03,080 --> 02:23:05,355
And we have great confidence...

2035
02:23:05,560 --> 02:23:09,189
...that in the final hour,
our mayor will be there for us.

2036
02:23:23,160 --> 02:23:24,434
And Tony...

2037
02:23:25,240 --> 02:23:26,229
Know this.

2038
02:23:26,480 --> 02:23:28,835
Wherever you go, you will always be...

2039
02:23:30,000 --> 02:23:32,753
...loved and greatly respected.

2040
02:23:34,680 --> 02:23:35,635
Thank you.

2041
02:23:37,360 --> 02:23:40,591
Thanks for helping me understand again
what I had forgotten.

2042
02:23:43,840 --> 02:23:45,353
Tony D.!

2043
02:24:03,880 --> 02:24:05,233
He's been here 30 years!

2044
02:24:05,640 --> 02:24:07,915
Even the dogs are sad, he said.

2045
02:24:11,400 --> 02:24:14,995
It's been way too long
not to win a big one.

2046
02:24:16,480 --> 02:24:19,631
San Francisco sure
took care of that for us.

2047
02:24:26,480 --> 02:24:30,029
In football, as in life, things change.

2048
02:24:32,920 --> 02:24:37,436
I guess it's time for me to get the
hell out of the way, bring in the new.

2049
02:24:38,120 --> 02:24:41,351
I like Nick Crozier.
I think he'll do a great job.

2050
02:24:46,040 --> 02:24:49,794
But most of all I want to thank
the people of Miami...

2051
02:24:51,760 --> 02:24:56,117
...for their support through
the last 20-some odd years.

2052
02:24:56,640 --> 02:24:58,153
Gee, it just flew by.

2053
02:25:02,240 --> 02:25:04,231
It's really meant a lot to me.

2054
02:25:08,160 --> 02:25:09,878
It meant everything to me.

2055
02:25:11,240 --> 02:25:14,596
I've had a great, great ride,
believe me. And...

2056
02:25:14,800 --> 02:25:16,233
And I'm gonna miss you.

2057
02:25:17,360 --> 02:25:20,113
He's an arrogant son of a bitch,
but I'll miss him.

2058
02:25:23,000 --> 02:25:25,070
In thinking about change...

2059
02:25:25,880 --> 02:25:30,396
...I don't know, I felt maybe it was
time for me to make a change too.

2060
02:25:30,840 --> 02:25:35,516
And it was Willie Beamen taught me
how to give it another shot.

2061
02:25:38,520 --> 02:25:40,112
So starting today...

2062
02:25:40,920 --> 02:25:42,592
...l'm taking over as head coach...

2063
02:25:42,840 --> 02:25:46,879
...for that new expansion team in
Albuquerque, New Mexico, the Aztecs.

2064
02:25:48,080 --> 02:25:52,232
"Why, " do you say? Because they're
giving me full management control.

2065
02:25:53,840 --> 02:25:57,071
But hoping not to make a complete fool
of myself out there...

2066
02:25:57,400 --> 02:26:00,597
...I just signed Willie Beamen
as my starting quarterback...

2067
02:26:00,800 --> 02:26:03,314
...and franchise player for the Aztecs.

2068
02:26:04,920 --> 02:26:09,311
So, Miss P, I look forward to seeing you
next season across those sidelines.

2069
02:26:13,200 --> 02:26:15,236
So long... Au revoir...

2070
02:26:16,440 --> 02:26:18,795
See you when the clouds come home.

2071
02:26:20,720 --> 02:26:23,837
Especially you, baby.
Smoking cigars on me now, are you?

2072
02:26:24,920 --> 02:26:26,035
Gotcha!

2073
02:26:29,920 --> 02:26:31,751
Thought we had him tied up!

2074
02:27:50,000 --> 02:27:51,069
All right, little man!

2075
02:27:51,320 --> 02:27:53,390
What's up? What's your name?

2076
02:27:54,520 --> 02:27:57,034
Hey, what up, man? What up? What up?

2077
02:28:00,080 --> 02:28:01,593
How y'all feeling?

2078
02:28:04,600 --> 02:28:07,751
All right, now.
Y'all be looking out for the game now.



